{
  "text": "MM is one of the most common hematological malignancies that originates from the aberrant transformation and expansion of normal plasmablasts/plasmacells in the BM [CITATION_1] . MM is characterized by a strong interaction with BM microenvironment that supports tumor cell growth and spreading, and by aggressive bone destruction [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
